'2:17': [
{sup:1, word:"Daniel", lines:["Nebuchadnezzar&rsquo;s marvelous dream should have impressed him deeply, but because he was blinded by worldly glory and power and did not have a heart for God&rsquo;s interests, he could not understand the dream and eventually forgot it (vv. {Dan2:1|1}-{Dan2:3|3}). All the magicians, all the wise men of Babylon, and the Chaldeans were unable to tell him the dream (vv. {Dan2:4|4}-{Dan2:13|13}). However, there was a person named Daniel, who did not care for worldly glory and power, who set his heart on the spiritual things regarding God&rsquo;s interests on earth, and who had the right position, the right angle, and the intrinsic capacity within him to understand the dream. He did not have the dream, yet he received the vision from God concerning it (vv. {Dan2:17|17}-{Dan2:23|23}), and he interpreted it (vv. {Dan2:24|24}-{Dan2:45|45})."]},
{sup:"a", word:"Hananiah", vrefs:"Dan. 1:7; 3:12"},
],
